      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRINCE RUPERT (3) started at $4.40 last time and ran below expectations, finishing seventh over 1250m at Kempsey. Going up a level this time but he cannot be underestimated. LA PELAGO (2) finished a close fourth last start after being in the firing line on the corner over 1000m at Orange, an improvement on her ninth at Gosford the run before. Will enjoy a drop in class and can play a leading role. BRAZEN BRANDO (1) saluted at this track two runs ago. Not disgraced last time out when in contention on the turn before finishing second over 1005m at this track, beaten a neck. Has a good record at this course and distance, including two wins. Finds a suitable race and can play a major role. CLAN D'ORO (8) turned in a better run last start when fourth over 1021m at Murwillumbah. Suitably placed so can turn things around.",
